The paper focuses on Self-Adaptive Software (SAS) and proposes a novel framework for optimizing SAS at runtime using a feature model and Multi-Objective Evolutionary Algorithm (MOEA). This falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with the design and development of software systems. The use of MOEA and domain knowledge to guide the search also suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of reproduction operators, which is a concept in Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the evaluation of the framework on different scenarios and conflicting quality objectives suggests a connection to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
